  reading: the probe under-estimates ‖J_f‖₂ ≈2.6× at every ρ, so the
           implied C/F≈1 of tab:directional-margin is a PROBE ARTIFACT;
           the true C/F is ≈2.5 (roughly flat), NOT ≈1. C/F is a constant
           (the derivation's structural claim) but its value is ≈2.5, so
           the operator-norm bound ρ+Lip(f)=ρ+2.5(1−ρ) runs 2.5→1, riding
           the boundary only as ρ→1; ‘flat near 1’ lives in ρ_spec, not here.

